{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17473725","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17473725"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:13:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:13:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2712"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2712","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2712"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.26,0.3,0.01,0.4,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2712"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76733"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2712","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2712"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2712"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62226"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3413"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13197"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28539"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42550"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44090"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76733","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76733"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 4-year-old unvaccinated boy presents to the emergency department with a fever and a distinctive widespread, pruritic, clear fluid filled vesicular rash over his entire body including his scalp. He otherwise looks well. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following precautions will need to be undertaken when examining this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Droplet precautions","Airborne precautions","No precautions required","Contact precautions","Gloves only"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient clearly has \u003Cstrong\u003Echickenpox (varicella)\u003C/strong\u003E given the classic widespread vesicular rash. The key information is that he is unvaccinated, and varicella is primarily a vaccine preventable disease. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EVaricella is an acute febrile illness that presents with a rash. Incubation period can range from 10 - 21 days and children often present with fevers and other mild symptoms such as abdominal pain and headache. Lesions often initially present on the scalp and spread to the rest of the body. Absence of scalp lesions makes chickenpox less likely. Lesions often crust within 48 hours, and once all the lesions have crusted over the patient is no longer infective.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVaricella \u003C/strong\u003Eis transmitted through aerosolised droplets, therefore \u003Cstrong\u003Eairborne precautions\u003C/strong\u003E are required. This includes standard precautions AND an N95 respiratory AND an isolation negative pressure room.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther examples of diseases requiring airborne precautions include measles, tuberculosis and SARS. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDroplet precautions would only include a standard surgical mask, gloves and gown which will not protect against varicella.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EContact precautions include gloves and a gown, and is used in diseases such as infective gastroenteritis. \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Personal protective equipment is very important and identifying which diseases require increased precautions is important for the safety of the treating staff and other patients in the department","Varicella must be considered in an unvaccinated individual with the classical rash and fever"],"references":["Airborne Precautions - Minnesota Dept. of Health [Internet]. Health.state.mn.us. 2021 Available from: https://www.health.state.mn.us/facilities/patientsafety/infectioncontrol/pre/airborne.html","Kliegman, Robert., et al. Nelson Textbook of Pediatrics. Edition 20. Phialdelphia, PA: Elsevier, 2016.","Ather B, Mirza TM, Edemekong PF. Airborne Precautions. 2023 Mar 13. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30285363."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62226"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2712"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62226","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62226"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-04T19:29:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-04T20:11:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2712"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76733"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"